                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-05-23</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is not an easy book to read. The first 3 chapters are very heavy going with little in the way of productive examples. I was looking for a book that gave me the basics of XML with C#. I was not looking for a book that spent the first 3 chapters covering the basics of XML on its own. <P>Having said that, I think the authors do a fairly good job of covering the material that they are attempting to do. This is definitely an introduction to XML, though, and there are a lot of unanswered detail questions that you will obviously need to research in other books.<P>There are several mistakes in the quoted code, and the fact that the WROX site is no longer available makes this a tough book to work through. Fortunately my C# is good enough to spot most of the syntactical errors, but I pity someone who is new to C# too.<P>In a nutshell, this book is okay, but you're going to need a lot more than this to really get to grips with the stuff.<P>I'm going to look at a couple of the O'Reilly books...</span>
                  
